      "span_text": "Indeed, the frequency of haplotype 1 (p = 8.20610 [CITATION_1] ) and the minor alleles of each of the relevant SNPs (rs1800871, rs1800872, rs3024490 and rs1554286, p,0.05) were significantly higher among people using drinking water from wells/rivers compared to those who use water from boreholes (tables S4, S8)."
